The paper deals with multi-task learning in deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the optimization of multiple objectives, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The experiments in the paper involve image classification and segmentation tasks, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for multi-task learning, which is related to optimization techniques used in neural networks (cs.NE).
